Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-001
<dl>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot opens from Accessories category of Xfce's main menu
	<dt>Point your mouse cursor to the Applications Menu icon and click it</dt>
		<dd>A menu should drop down</dd>
	<dt>Select the Accessories option</dt>
		<dd>A drop down list should appear</dd>
	<dt>Select the Screenshot item</dt>
		<dd>The Screenshoot window should open</dd>
</dl>
Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-002
<dl>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot saves a screenshot of the whole screen as you see it
	<dt>Open Screenshoot</dt>
		<dd>The take a screenshoot window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Entire screen" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshoot action window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Save" option, under the 'Action' section and click the ok button</dt>
		<dd>A save dialog shoud be displayed, allowing to set the save location and the name of the file</dd>
</dl>
Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-003
<dl>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot copies a screenshot of the whole screen as you see it to the clipboard
	<dt>Open Screenshoot</dt>
		<dd>The take a screenshoot window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Entire screen" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshoot action window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Copy to the clipboard" option, under the 'Action' section and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshoot should be copied to the clipboard, allowing it to be pasted in another application</dd>
</dl>
Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-004
<dl>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot opens a copie of a screenshot of the whole screen as you see it with another application
	<dt>Open Screenshoot</dt>
		<dd>The take a screenshoot window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Entire screen" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshoot action window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Open with:" option, under the 'Action' section</dt>
		<dd>The drop-down list box should now be enabled and clickable</dd>
	<dt>Click on the drop-down list</dt>
		<dd>A list of available applications should drop down</dd>
	<dt>Select one of the available applications and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshot should be saved to the system's temporary directory and opened with the application chosen from the drop-down list</dd>
</dl>
Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-005
<dl>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot allows to host a copie of a screenshot of the whole screen as you see it on a free online hosting service
	<dt>Open Screenshoot</dt>
		<dd>The take a screenshoot window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Entire screen" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshoot action window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Host on ZimageZ" option, under the 'Action' section and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>ZimageZ dialog window should open</dd>
	<dt>Fill all the fields of ZimageZ dialog window and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshoot should be hosted on this free online hosting service, and easily shareable with other people</dd>
</dl>
Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-006
<dt>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot saves a screenshot of the active window
