Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-010
<dt>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot saves a screenshot by clicking and dragging a rectangle over a area of the screen, before releasing the mouse button
	<dt>Open Screenshoot</dt>
		<dd>The take a screenshoot window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Select a region" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screen should darken</dd>
	<dt>Click the left mouse button and drag a rectangle over a area of the screen, before releasing the mouse button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshoot action window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select the "Save" option, under the 'Action' section and click the ok button</dt>
		<dd>A save dialog shoud be displayed, allowing to set the save location and the name of the file</dd>
</dt>
