Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-014
<dl>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot allows to select whether or not the screenshot will include the mouse pointer
	<dt>Open Screenshoot</dt>
		<dd>The take a screenshoot window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select one of the options, under the 'Region to capture', tick the "Capture the mouse pointer" option section and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshoot action window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Select one of the options, under the 'Action' section and click the ok button</dt>
		<dd>The saved screenshoot should include the mouse pointer</dd>
</dl>
Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-015
<dl>
	This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshoot allows to set the delay that will elapse between pressing the "OK" button and screenshot being taken
	<dt>Open Screenshoot</dt>
		<dd>The take a screenshoot window should be displayed</dd>
	<dt>Point the mouse pointer to the textbox's top arrow button, under the 'Delay before capturing'</dt>
		<dd>The number of seconds should increase accordingly</dd>
	<dt>Select one of the options, under the 'Region to capture' and click the OK button</dt>
		<dd>The screenshot active window should only be displayed after the number of established seconds has elapsed</dd>
</dl>
<strong>If all actions produce the expected results listed, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
    If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> 'failed' and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result</strong>
